":"Section","source":{"title":"Photographing live coral fragments"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8406233EB1694B60ACC8A260F682808A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For detailed instructions on how to photograph coral fragments, please refer to Section 1 of our published protocol: Geometric Method for Estimating Coral Surface Area Using Image Analysis (<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.bpxcmpiw\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.bpxcmpiw<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \":UNDERLINE;\">)<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250617,"guid":"2DA23CF015AF11ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250616,"previous_guid":"E5E18E2015AE11ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"497E02F2990B45ACAA897864225C1F77","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Photographing live coral fragments"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BA55A34BC2F64B1E9A5ADE9634E7A74E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Additional notes: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Use diffused lighting when photographing corals to minimize harsh shadows or glare from the wet tissue surface as these will preclude accurate color image analysis. For more information on how to diffuse light, check out <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/Diffuse-Light\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">this wikiHow<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">It is essential that the coral colony and the reference card receive the same uniform illumination\/light field. <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">If possible, coral colonies should be imaged from multiple angles in order to get a good representation of bleaching degree and colony color.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250618,"guid":"B905DF8015B011ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250617,"previous_guid":"2DA23CF015AF11ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"151D2A05589B42CEAB4E634AC270B1C1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9BACD75F77394A50B18A07DA96A29A8B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Download ImageJ. ImageJ can be downloaded for free from the NIH website: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/imagej.nih.gov\/ij\/download.html\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">https:\/\/imagej.nih.gov\/ij\/download.html<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250619,"guid":"CB08C62015B011ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250618,"previous_guid":"B905DF8015B011ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9FC8F5D4EBB74028AC8A993726B2E246","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"22BA6E9513DA42FC978ED1AA832154A3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Import the first photograph of either the top (Fig. 1A) or the side (Fig. 1B) of the coral into the ImageJ software. <\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edx77bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"6C71F839C610440ABF115336350EB0AF","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edx77bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250620,"guid":"99F3A90015B111ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250619,"previous_guid":"CB08C62015B011ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3B359D6F63984989A50736556D9C19A6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5922A718816647959848815D6946C836","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Convert the color to 8-bit greyscale. Press \"Image\" > \"Type\" > \"8-bit\" (Fig. 2). The color image should now convert to black and white.<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyb7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"5D5C980EDBC84EFDA139870F5750BA70","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyb7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250621,"guid":"F345DF0015B111ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250620,"previous_guid":"99F3A90015B111ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0FD029AB505345F8A59F2C7F95C63901","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A57CE9FBAAE4455D8D810DC286F3958D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Using the hand tool and the zoom function (zoom shortcuts: Ctrl and + on PC keyboard, or left-click and scroll on PC mouse), zoom in and adjust the position of the image such that the coral fragment takes up all of the ImageJ window (Fig. 3).  Select the \"Oval\" tool from the toolbar (second button from the left). Draw a circle on the image (small blue circle shown in Fig. 3). Take care to avoid regions of the coral that are in a shadow or reflecting light due to glare from wet tissue.<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyf7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"4CC8252D0DE3490A8306494A597FFBFF","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyf7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250622,"guid":"D3B502A015B211ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250621,"previous_guid":"F345DF0015B111ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4E8C8E54C79B4C588944BF4D9B009443","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9BFD575A85E549089A7E812C97DB6BA0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Next, navigate to the \"Set Measurements\" option by pressing \"Analyze\" > \"Set Measurements\" (Fig. 4).<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyj7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"293B3D739A294B87864EFB5092EA6365","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyj7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250623,"guid":"2E41665015B311ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250622,"previous_guid":"D3B502A015B211ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"BB805079B0FA4D1CB90192BE4F86D20D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9FAAD04B26F4495396130950FF949B2E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Select the box next to \"Mean grey value\" (Fig. 5.)<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyp7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"06A899733E524B259D73741E506CA9A1","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyp7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250624,"guid":"5FD003C015B311ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250623,"previous_guid":"2E41665015B311ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3156E421204643B9A83F38416774974C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FA354FD242374E01B9BA99F32F30A0F9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Next, navigate to the toolbar, press \"Analyze\" followed by \"Measure\" [keyboard shortcut is Ctrl + M] (Fig. 6). This will bring up a Results window of the X and Y coordinates mean grey value for the region selected within the blue circle (Fig. 6).<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyt7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"9C3DA64786444FBCB39C3CA245276654","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyt7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250629,"guid":"B95E586015B311ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250624,"previous_guid":"5FD003C015B311ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8A780B6FFD4144BB9BD5FF8F3E65F7A3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6FB47B1616D442A6A01D5B701D25335D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Next, draw a new circle somewhere different on the coral surface (Fig. 7). Again make sure to avoid areas with shadows and\/or glare. Measure this new area (Fig. 7).<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyx7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"DE01F9F40E4A4E238783F94EA773A1AE","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edyx7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250630,"guid":"0A3BA3A015B411ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250629,"previous_guid":"B95E586015B311ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"FBB8F82646DC4B6B959C82664FD013C2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"885EC34AC7FD471D932A438272DA59F9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Repeat the previous step until 5 different coral circle areas have been measured. Then draw a circle on the white standard (paper background in this example) (Fig. 8). Make sure the size of the circle drawn is similar in size to the previously drawn coral circles. Ensure you avoid areas of the white standard which have shadows, glare, or dirt specks.<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edy37bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"2A5FFEDDC1304F61B04C41A61F7B8199","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edy37bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250631,"guid":"B46A88A015B411ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250630,"previous_guid":"0A3BA3A015B411ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"55F427508BE648E4AE2D534C874C6002","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"002DF5475B6C4EFC90F93091CA26840D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Repeat the previous steps, and measure five new coral areas, and one new reference standard area (Fig. 9). Make sure to always draw circles in new areas (i.e., do not accidentally measure the grey value of the same coral polyps twice).<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edy77bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"E4F6DB79157748EC917064A3A19ED1EE","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edy77bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250632,"guid":"219EC58015B511ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250631,"previous_guid":"B46A88A015B411ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B77540969FB34C6F9D6A35A345611AE5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"366EF3FE582F4402B198DBBBAB505136","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Copy the twelve Mean Value Grey values and paste them into a excel spreadsheet (Fig. 10).<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzb7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A411EC85FDDC4A36A64B740C40F6323F","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzb7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250633,"guid":"80D3548015B511ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250632,"previous_guid":"219EC58015B511ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DDDCD14ED37F4C52BD7C8539F9C47EFB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DE7D1BDDB63D4DC4AFE8E9716A3DCBF6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For increased replication, repeat steps 4 through 13 with the side view image (Fig. 1B). Copy and paste values next to those from the top view (Fig. 11).<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzf7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"1BB076CFFE094F608B7BF419FC075668","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzf7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250634,"guid":"EEA4469015B511ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250633,"previous_guid":"80D3548015B511ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"580815E8FF374BA599AE71748B061D9D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7150182E8C374A67A5FF06CE98F3B3D4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Normalize the coral Mean Grey Values to the white reference standard Mean Grey Values using the equation shown in Fig. 12. Normalize the following coral values to the following white reference standard values:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">coral circles #1  \u2013  #5 normalize to White Std1<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">coral circles #6  \u2013 #10 normalize to White Std2<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">coral circles #11 \u2013 #15 normalize to White Std3<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">coral circles #16 \u2013 #20 normalize to White Std4<\/li><\/ul><\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzj7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"E4FE818A99AE4539893A898F729DE265","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzj7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250635,"guid":"3662B60015B711ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250636,"previous_guid":"4EDF53A015B711ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7BF4054365BE4580B46738A8ADF86FD6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8A8F65A11CD249AABDEADCA83A21ABD4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For an example of how to set up your spreadsheet, see attachment. <\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"49EC3CA015B711ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","order_id":2,"type_id":23,"title":"file","source":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edq87bqe.xlsx","placeholder":"","original_name":"Example spreadsheet.xlsx"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250636,"guid":"4EDF53A015B711ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250634,"previous_guid":"EEA4469015B511ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"39B854098FC0403680E92310ADF25667","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6ED92B4262F2435BAA4D0793EE6D39D9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Calculate the mean intensity grey (MIG) and standard deviation of the 20 normalized values (Fig. 13).<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzp7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"5B7769DAE5B1439BB34DCCF67E9C8753","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzp7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1250637,"guid":"66D3B90015B811ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","previous_id":1250635,"previous_guid":"3662B60015B711ECADF0AB70F3EF8F3C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6DAAACF9E46C454E984658E6D0B8DCAD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Image analysis of mean grey value"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"01FE6DE12F0149698AB81907AC99754A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This method is particularly useful when comparing experimental control and treatment corals colonies, photographed at similar times, using the same lighting (Fig. 14).<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzt7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"108EBA9839AE4C54B8DE16BCB59CD276","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/edzt7bqe.jpg\" \/><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol outlines a method of quantitatively measuring the degree of bleaching of a coral colony non-destructively in the field using image analysis. Previous studies have shown that mean intensity grey (MIG), also known as percent whiteness, is highly correlated with chlorophyll<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> a<\/span><span> and Symbiodiniaceae density (Chow et al. 2016, Amid et al. 2018), and therefore can be used to quantify the bleaching intensity of a coral colony. Color analysis can be done using digital photographs of live coral colonies either <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">in situ <\/span><span>(e.g., Maguire et al. 2003) or <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">ex-situ<\/span><span> in the lab (Amid et al. 2018; this protocol). Photographs must be taken prior to any preservation or processing of tissue, such as freezing, use of preservatives or fixatives, airbrushing etc., to ensure no alteration of the original coral color occurs. In this protocol, corals are photographed in front of a white reference standard and the resulting color images are subsequently converted to 8-bit greyscale and analyzed.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\">There are two steps to this protocol:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1) Photographing live coral fragments<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">2) Image analysis of mean grey value<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol was written by Dr. Rowan McLachlan and was reviewed by Dr. Andr\u00e9a Grottoli.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">Acknowledgments<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">I would like to thank Dr. Eugene Katrukha for kindly taking the time to teach me this method, and providing me feedback on how to produce higher quality images for analysis. <\/div><br\/><br\/><br\/><br\/><\/div>","changed_on":1631745401}